		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So I pick up some nice super famicom games at a market for a great price and I want to play them in English.<br />So I was thinking of making them into repro but keeping the carts with the original artwork.<br /><br />I got dragon quest 5, 6 and final fantasy 6.<br /><br />My first question is where is safe to download roms?<br />I used one site to download dragon quest 5 and the file size was 1.5mb I then patched it and it didn't work.<br />So I then downloaded a patched rom and it works fine but has a bad checksum and no header and was 2mb<br /><br />Now I didn't want to do a load of wiring so I got some TSOP boards and 29f033 chips.<br /><br />So I think I have to pad the rom in order for it to work on the chip.<br />Will Lunar Expand work and will the rom need the to have the header or not and what about the checksum when padding?<br /><br />So once the rom is 4mb I most remove the header using UCON and should I make sure the checksum should be ok and then it is ready to burn?<br /><br />I also plan to add the super cic to each cart as I only have an unmodded PAL SNES, so will the games run in 50 or 60hz?<br /><br />Is there anything I am missing?<br /><br />Thanks in advance <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

